notesStmt.note: On fol. 1a: "al-Sīrah li-Yaḥyá al-Zaydī" in pencil in Arabic script.
Ms. erroneously foliated: second leaf is skipped. Record follows erroneous numbering.

Physical description: 33 lines per page; written in small naskhi in black on white glazed, laid European paper. Rubrication and catchwords; text framed in red border. Headings in large red script. A few marginal notes and corrections. Text on fol. 2a-97b.

msContents.summary: Acephalous anon. work by a Zaydī author of the 6th/7th cent. H. There are frequent references to Shams al-Dīn Jaʻfar ibn Aḥmad ibn ʻAbd al-Salām (d. 573/ 1177: Brockelmann, GAL, I, 508) from whom the author received traditions. The book is divided into ten bābs (the beginning of the first bāb is missing).

msItem.title: al-Bāb al-thānī fī al-ḥaml bi-hi wa-mawlidih
al-Bāb al-ʻāshir fī akhbār Abī al-Ḥusayn Zaydi ibn ʻAlī ibn al-Ḥusayn

origin.p: Copy completed and validated in Jumādá al-Awwal 1080 H. [October 1669], with the support of Yaḥyá ibn al-Ḥusayn ibn Amīr al-Muʾminīn al-Qāsim ibn Muḥammad ibn ʻAlī (d. after 1687) (fol. 97b).
